This PR fixes the add bid subcommand of both `make-transaction` and `put-transaction` to allow users to specify the minimum and maximum delegation amounts.

Additionally, this PR allows for the optional toggling of the `casper-types` feature `std-fs-io` by consumers of the clients library.

## Example

For this example command:
```
casper-client make-transaction add-bid --delegation-rate 10 --public-key /path/to/public_key_hex --transaction-amount 10 --min-amount 10 --max-amount 100 --payment-amount 100 --gas-price-tolerance 10 --secret-key /path/to/secret_key.pem --chain-name test --pricing-mode fixed

```


